15. d4 {We strike before Black can bring his knight back into the game. We will not hesitate to play g4 at the right moment. Black has to make a tough decision here. I have shown this position to a few of my GM friends and no one was able to equalize cleanly.} 
15. a6 {Black should aim for quick piece activity rather than trying to save his e5 pawn. Black has definite compensation due to the bishop pair but he should act swiftly.} 
16. b6
16. cxb6 {I feel this is more likely to happen in most of the games. Black has captured away from the center and we should use this to try to gain control over the center.} 
17. dxe5
17. b5
18. Rd1 {We gain a tempo forcing the queen to c7 where it would come under attack in the future after Ne3-d5. You can check out more details here.} 
