8. Be2 {Knight on the rim is dim! Black has to develop his kingside quickly and in the meantime, we will win the pawn on d4 and bring out our queenside pieces. The knight on a5 is a long-term issue for Black; we do not need to try and exploit it immediately. Ideas such as b4 are always hanging in the air.} 
