[Result "*"]

1. e4
1. e5
2. Nf3
2. Nc6
3. Bc4
3. d6 {I always thought that this was just a lazy attempt to sidestep theory and confuse us. But then I faced this against Gukesh in the finals of the Chess Super League (CSL) 2021 and ended up losing a painful game. Black keeps his options open regarding his kingside development.} 
4. d4 {As usual, our approach is to go for a direct play in the center with d2-d4. Black may try to trick us by going after our center with moves like Bg4, but these are rarely so effective with the black king still in the center.} 
4. Bg4 {is surprisingly the most played move in the position. Bg4 in most cases is just bad in the Italian because the Bishop will get kicked around with h3 and either Nd2-f1-g3 or direct g4. The knight still being on b1 ready to run to the kingside is an additional issue for Black here.} 
5. h3
5. Bh5
6. d5 {We can close the center and force the knight to waste further time. We have a big space advantage. We are a lot of tempo up compared to King's Indian type of positions.} 
6. Nb8
7. Be3 {We follow up with g4, Nc3, and the fact that we have not played c4 works in our favour. This is because once we go for the move c4, our pieces get restricted and it is time-consuming to go for the c5-break. We can start an attack on the kingside targeting the g6-bishop.} 
