7. Nbd2 {Why do we do this instead of the usual a4?   1) The knight belongs on e3 exploiting the weakness on f5 and also keeping an eye on the d5-square. The usual route- Nd2-f1-e3 is not possible with the rook on f1 and we are preparing the alternate route via c4   2) One of Black's main ideas is to go for d5 gaining space in the center. Now d5 can be met with the strong d4 blowing open the center in our favour.   3) It helps us go d3-d4 without worrying about exd4 cxd4 d5/Ne4 type of ideas.} 
7. Bg7
8. Bb3 {One thing we need to remember here is to NOT play Re1 for two reasons-   1) We may need the square for the knight after g5-g4   2) The rook may get active in the future along the 'f' line after a potential f2-f3/f4.   Another thing which I keep stressing on throughout the course- NEVER play h3 in these positions after O-O unless Black has also castled.} 
8. a6 {Has been played by a few strong players. Black wants to wait for Nc4 before going Be6. This is because the structure with fxe6 is not that great for Black, especially with the bishop on g7.} 
9. Nc4
9. Be6 {After every opponent's move we have to try to understand it's drawback. My coach called this the drawback principle. Usually we should spend atleast a brief amount of time to understand if anything has changed significantly after our opponent's last move.} 
10. d4 {We do not miss such chances to break in the center.} 
10. exd4
11. Nxd4 {Our knight on f3 is only restricting our position. In these g5-lines, it makes a lot of sense to capture with the knight on d4 as g4 is always hanging in the air. Also it gives us the possibility to go for f4 in the future.} 
11. Nxd4
12. cxd4
12. d5 {The only way for Black. With the king in the center, he has to go for such an operation which is very hard to do in an over-the-board game.} 
13. Na5
13. b6 {Is the most natural move.} 
14. Ba4+
14. b5
15. e5 {If we are able to retreat with the bishop next we will get a big advantage with our center.} 
15. bxa4
16. exf6
16. Bxf6
17. Nb7 {We get our knight to the outpost on c5 and we also have the idea of f2-f4 coming up.} 
