9. h3 {Our plan is simple- Re1, Nd2-f1-g3. This is the drawback of the move O-O. We are able to play h3 and continue with our normal plans without worrying about a kingside attack.} 
9. a5 {Engines like this move a lot in these lines. But it does not create any real threat to change our plan.} 
10. Re1
10. Nh5
11. Nf1
11. Nf4
12. Ng3 {We are now prepared to go for d4 next.} 
12. Qf6
13. Nh2 {We step away from g4 kind of ideas and we can maybe bring our knight to e3 next via g4.} 
13. Qg6
14. Bc2
14. Be6
15. Be3 {And next we go d3-d4. Black does not have any good plan. His pieces look good but do not really achieve much. We have better control over the center and a juicy f5-square.} 
