6. a6 {This is the main, traditional setup for Black in the Italian and it can happen via different move orders. Here Black delays O-O for a few reasons-   1) Bg5 lines are less effective for us but we do not go for them anyway.   2) Black is hoping for White to commit the move h3 after which he can start an immediate attack with h6-g5.} 
