12. Nf4 {This is the most natural continuation of Black's plan.} 
13. Ng4
13. Qg6
14. Bxf4 {This is a great exchange for us as we get a majority in the center and the f4 pawn will always be a weakness.} 
14. exf4
15. d4 {This is the key point. We are ready to give up the h3 pawn in return for a great center that totally restricts Black's minor pieces. Also, we will get opposite colour bishop middlegame where the attacking side always has a big edge. We can go for e5 at the right moment.} 
15. Bxg4
16. hxg4
16. Qxg4
17. b4 {We gain total control over the queenside too. The bishop on a7 will start to feel the heat soon.} 
17. Ne7
18. b5 {This further stops Black from being able to go for c6 and d5. The bishop on a7 is a sorry sight.} 
18. axb5
19. axb5 {We can go for Qb3 next putting further pressure on the f7-pawn. Also then we can double on the 'a' file.} 
