11. Re8 {The main move.} 
12. Qc2 {We keep an eye on the e4 pawn and prepare to go for Nc4 in the future. We also get out of the 'd' file. One of my coaches had this concept called- Overprotection of the central squares, taken from the book "My System". The concept is that we need to have our pieces in contact with the center since most of the action usually revolves around the center. At some point, our pieces will get activated.} 
12. Bc7
13. b4
13. d5 {Looks typical but does not work that well.} 
14. exd5
14. exd4
15. Rxe8+
15. Qxe8
16. dxc6
16. dxc3
17. Qxc3
17. Qxc6
18. Qxc6
18. bxc6
19. Nc4 {And we are much better positionally. We can continue with Be3-c5. Black's pawn structure is ruined and we can slowly start attacking the queenside pawns.} 
