12. d4 {The first part of our plan is complete - we have secured control over the center. Now we have to maintain the control and finish our development.} 
12. c6
13. Bf1 {The bishop is well placed here, both in defence and offence. Bishops are long range pieces and they do not need to always be in the most active squares.} 
13. h6
14. Qc2 {Now that the queen is out of the way, we want to take on e5 next.} 
14. Qc7
15. Nbd2 {Our plan could be to play b3, Nc4 and Rd1.} 
15. a4 {Black wants to stop our plan.} 
16. c4
