7. Ba7 {One key rule to remember in the a6 system- NEVER go h3 before Black has castled on the kingside. h3 creates a hook on the kingside for Black to break with g5-g4.} 
8. Re1
8. O-O
9. h3
9. Kh8 {This creative idea gained popularity back in 2019 and was played by many top players. But it was abandoned soon after. Black wants to go Ng8 and f5 next.} 
10. d4 {Of course, we meet every one of these unprincipled lines with our favourite central break. We will go Be3 next if given the chance.} 
10. Ng8 {The continuation of the plan.} 
11. b4 {We give up the pawn on b4 in order to gain a few tempi. Black has to do something quickly as we are threatening b4-b5.} 
11. exd4 {Black has to go for the pawn as otherwise we just get everything we need for free.} 
12. cxd4
12. Nxb4
