23. Rxe3
23. Nf6
24. Rae1 {We are ready to go h5 next having stopped the move Ne7.} 
24. h5 {Drastic situations call for drastic measures. The only move to hold his kingside.} 
25. Bxg6 {The resulting pawn structure is very dangerous for Black as our knight can come to g5 and create mating nets. Also, we get the 7th rank for our rook.} 
25. fxg6
26. Re7 {We can go Qd3 next targeting the g6-pawn. In the future, we have an amazing square on g5 for our knight.} 
