6. Be6 {This is too early. Black anyway has to play a few necessary moves such as O-O, a6. Going for Be6 without the move a6 means that the bishop will be forced to go to b6 which is an inferior square. Also here White can make use of his development to start quick play on the queenside and the center.} 
7. Bxe6 {As a rule in the Bc5 Italian, we always capture on e6 the instant Black goes for it. This is the whole reason for the revival of the Italian.} 
7. fxe6
8. b4 {We gain a lot of space with tempo on the queenside.} 
8. Bb6
9. a4
9. a6
