10. Re8 {This is one of the most common and critical lines at the top level in the Italian. Black is extremely solid and does not want to make any unnecessary weaknesses by directly going Be6. His aim is usually to go Be6 next and recapture with the rook, followed by an eventual d5.} 
11. b4 {Once Black has played Re8 we can go for b4 as it is clear that he should likely go for the Be6 plan. Always go for the most necessary move first and b4 is the most useful move here for White.} 
