15. Ra1 {We have two plans here. One is to go Nb3 next followed by Bd2 and c4. In case Black goes for d5 we can also go for Be3 to exploit the weakness on c5. Black usually tries to go for Nh5-f4 and Rf6. We will try to meet Nh5 with Nh4. The other plan is to go for our usual Nf1-g3-f5 and create play on the kingside.} 
15. Rae8 {Has been played by Hikaru twice. It is pretty similar to Rd8 although I feel the rook was better placed on d8.} 
16. Nb3
16. Bb6
17. a5 {We do the same as in the Rd8-variation(link). We get a tempo and then exchange the bishops.} 
17. Ba7
18. Be3
18. Bxe3
19. Rxe3
19. Nh5
20. Kh2 {We can go either d4 or play slowly with g3, Nh4 next.} 
20. Nf4
21. g3
21. Ng6
22. Rd1 {We prepare to go d4 next. The rooks are useless on the 'e' file and Black has to probably play Rd8 here anyway. We have decent pressure here.} 
