17. Ng3
17. Rad8
18. Bd2 {Ideally our plan next would be to go Qc1, Nf5 and Bxh6 in some order, but the problem is that the f5-square is unstable and Black can take twice on e4 when we go for Nf5 and Qc1. So we have to be clever about it. As long as the queen is on c2 we can go for Nf5 without having to worry about any tactics.The same idea does not work after Bd2 as e4 is well protected.} 
18. Qe6 {The queen is perfect here keeping an eye on the kingside and also on the c4-square as we will see in some of the lines.} 
19. Nf5
19. Bb6 {This is pretty logical as the bishop was a weakness on a7 if White took on b5. On the other hand, we can always go a5 pushing the bishop back, and it is not clear in whose favour the inclusion of move a5 is.} 
20. a5
20. Ba7
21. Rac1 {A cunning move. This is one of the engine's top choices. Initially, I did not understand this move at all. But then I compared the Bxh6-variation with and without Rac1 and it became pretty clear. Now in the same exact line after Black goes Qd2, our queen is protected.} 
21. Kh8
22. Be3 {There is nothing else we can do. We claim that the king on h8 is worse than on g8 and our rook is better on c1.} 
22. Bxe3
23. Nxe3 {We have some small edge in the position. We can take twice on d5 and put pressure on the e5-pawn.} 
