10. Bxe6
10. fxe6
11. b4 {Again pretty similar to the Bc5 main lines. We go for b4 there too gaining space on the queenside.} 
11. Qe8
12. c3 {We cover the d4-square and also prepare to go for d4 or a4 in the future. Another upcoming plan is to go Ra2 covering the 2nd rank.} 
12. Nh5
13. Ra2 {Another idea borrowed from the Bxe6, fxe6-lines which we have seen in the c3, d3 chapters. We defend the f2-pawn and also have ideas of utilizing the rook along the second rank.} 
13. Nf4
14. Re1
14. Qh5
15. Nh2 {We are okay with exchanging the queens.} 
15. Qxd1
16. Rxd1 {We have a slight edge in the endgame. We can take on f4 and go g3, Kg2. Black has no real counterplay and he has to keep reacting to our plans.} 
