12. Nxe4
12. d5
13. Bd3
13. dxe4
14. Bxe4 {The bishop is very well placed here. The semi-open 'f' file is a big bonus for us, and we have better control over the center.} 
14. Be6
15. c3 {Having a space advantage, we should try to keep more minor pieces on the board. We give some room for our bishop along the b1-h7 diagonal and also defend our pawn on d4.} 
