1. e4
1. e5 {I knew Sethu anna quite well before this game and he is usually very well prepared. But at the same time I also knew that he often takes a lot of risk with the Black pieces to unbalance the game. So I was expecting something along the lines of Sicilian Najdorf or Taimanov but he did really surprise me by going for 1...e5.} 
