10. b4
10. Nh7 {No surprise really. The latest trend and the top choice of most of the computers.} 
11. Rf1 {I remembered that both the moves Kh1 and Rf1 were good in this position. I did not remember anything more and after this point I was playing on my own. But one thing I did was to play very quickly acting like I knew the position very well. This worked well for me but I would not recommend this approach unless you really have a lot of experience in the opening.} 
11. Qf6
12. Kh1 {This is not necessary here and I actually knew that. But I also wanted to get out of his preparation.} 
12. Ne7 {is the usual plan in these positions but it is a bit early here as it allows us to go d4 easily.} 
13. d4 {We are of course not worried about Black capturing our pawn. We will be delighted if Black opens up the center.} 
13. Ng6
