28. Qd7
29. Nh4 {Both sides have played very accurately for the last 10 moves. But time trouble is approaching and we see mistakes starting to happen. This is another benefit for White. Black's king is much more exposed and these time scrambles usually tend to favour White.} 
29. Bf7
30. Bb5
30. Qxe7
31. Rxe7
31. Bd5 {Is too careless.} 
32. Nh5 {All of a sudden it becomes very difficult for Black to react to our kingside attack even without the queens on the board. This is the problem with neglecting some of your pieces (a7 and b6).} 
32. Nc8
33. Rxg7
33. Bxd4
34. Bd3
34. Bg8
35. Nf5 {And it is already very difficult.} 
35. Nd6 {The final blunder in time trouble.} 
36. Nxd4
